### Anything else?

It seems that there is some sort of handshake communication between the backend and content scripts of the Angular DevTools extension using the message event which seems to be putting the process in a loop that madly triggers the change detection on the app.

In my use case I could not put the listener outside Angular Zone because what listens to the message event is a library (pdftron) that executes addEventListener by simply requiring the package.

```ts
import {WebViewer} from '@pdftron/webviewer';
console.log(WebViewer);
// window.addEventListener executed
```

The only workaround would be to use Zone flags but first I need to make sure the library does not rely on the message event on its Angular sdk.

